					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Year 16.</p>						

						<p>This inscription engraved in characters of the 11th century A.D. does not mention any king. This records the gift of land (as <hi rend="italic">kuḍinīṅgā-dēvadāna</hi>) made tax-free, entrusted to Nāraṇan Kāḍaṉ, by the inhabitants of Perumuḻai for food and other offerings to the value of 10 <hi rend="italic">akkam</hi> in the temple. </p>						

						</summary>
